  "notes": [
    {
      "title": "Emphatic Nūn (نون التوكيد)",
      "titleArabic": "نون التوكيد",
      "content": [
        "The emphatic nūn (nūn al-tawkīd) is attached to present tense and imperative verbs for emphasis. It has two forms: heavy (ثقيلة) with shaddah and light (خفيفة) without."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "Heavy nūn: لَيَكْتُبَنَّ (with shaddah)",
        "Light nūn: لَيَكْتُبَنْ (sukūn)",
        "Makes the verb mabnī (indeclinable)",
        "Used after لَ of oath, with commands/prohibitions"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "وَاللهِ لأَفْعَلَنَّ", "english": "By Allah, I will surely do it" },
        { "arabic": "لَا تَفْعَلَنَّ ذَلِكَ", "english": "Do not ever do that" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Estimated Case Endings (الإعراب التقديري)",
      "titleArabic": "الإعراب التقديري",
      "content": [
        "Some nouns have estimated (latent) case endings because the final letter cannot show the short vowel. These include maqṣūr, manqūṣ, and nouns with attached yā' al-mutakallim."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "Maqṣūr (الْفَتَى): ends in alif - all endings estimated",
        "Manqūṣ (الْقَاضِي): ends in yā' - raf'/jarr estimated, naṣb apparent",
        "With yā' al-mutakallim (كِتَابِي): endings estimated"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "جَاءَ الْفَتَى", "english": "The young man came (estimated ḍammah)" },
        { "arabic": "رَأَيْتُ الْقَاضِيَ", "english": "I saw the judge (apparent fatḥah)" }
      ]
    }
  ],
